\begin{frame}[c, fragile]{Use Version Control}
Git is intimidating, but it's the best tool available.

If you feel uncomfortable with Git use any automated solutions, like this R snippet (but seriously "use git"):

<<archive, eval=FALSE>>=
zip(
  # working directory + date + zip = archive file
  paste0(dirname(getwd()), "/",
         Sys.Date(),
         basename(getwd()),
         ".zip"),
  # archive all files in current directory
  getwd()
)
@

\end{frame}

